.TH HYPRLOCK 1 "2025-11-21" "hyprlock 0.9.2" "Hyprland Ecosystem"
.SH NAME
hyprlock \- Hyprland's GPU\-accelerated screen locking utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hyprlock
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hyprlock
is a simple, multi\-threaded, GPU\-accelerated screen locking utility for
Hyprland.
It uses the ext\-session\-lock Wayland protocol to lock the session.
.PP
Features include blurred screenshot backgrounds, gradient borders,
animations, shadows, fractional scaling support, and native fingerprint
authentication through libfprint.
.PP
Without a configuration file,
.B hyprlock
renders a black screen but still locks the session.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-config " " \fIfile\fR
Specify the configuration file to use.
.TP
.BR \-\-display " " \fIname\fR
Specify the Wayland display to connect to.
.TP
.BR \-\-grace " " \fIseconds\fR
Set the grace period in seconds before requiring authentication.
During the grace period, any input dismisses the lock screen.
.TP
.BR \-\-immediate\-render
Do not wait for resources before drawing the background.
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-fade\-in
Disable the fade\-in animation when the lock screen appears.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose logging.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Disable logging.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Show version information.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file is searched for at
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/hypr/hyprlock.conf
or
.IR ~/.config/hypr/hyprlock.conf .
.SS General options
.TP
.B hide_cursor
Hide the cursor on the lock screen. Default: 0.
.TP
.B ignore_empty_input
Do not show a failed attempt on empty password submission. Default: 0.
.TP
.B immediate_render
Render immediately without waiting for resources. Default: 0.
.TP
.B fail_timeout
Timeout in milliseconds after a failed authentication attempt. Default: 2000.
.SS Authentication
.TP
.B auth:pam:enabled
Enable PAM authentication. Default: 1.
.TP
.B auth:pam:module
PAM module name. Default: hyprlock.
.TP
.B auth:fingerprint:enabled
Enable fingerprint authentication via libfprint. Default: 0.
.SS Widgets
The following widget types are available for configuring the lock screen
appearance:
.BR background ,
.BR shape ,
.BR image ,
.BR input\-field ,
and
.BR label .
Each supports monitor selection, position, size, color, rounding, border,
shadow, and animation properties.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/pam.d/hyprlock
PAM configuration for hyprlock.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR hypridle (1),
.BR Hyprland (1),
.BR hyprctl (1)
